<subSubSection id="A313D288BEE63247273238F66EF1BFCF" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="83AE21560384456B8BA462ED429634F7" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName id="982E30AEF10F5A5DAD2F68BAFE1822A6" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus Poey</taxonomicName>
is the most speciose and geographically widespread genus of the Rivulidae, comprising about 100 valid species (Costa, 2003a, b, c; Costa, in press) occurring between southeastern Mexico (about 20° N) and northeastern Argentina (about 30° S). Some species groups have been suggested based upon apomorphic morphological features (Costa, 1991, 1995a, 1998, 2003c). One of these groups is an Amazonian clade diagnosed by a unique arrangement of frontal scales and the presence of an oblique infraorbital dark gray bar through chin, conditions not occurring in other rivulids (Costa, 2003c). It includes 
<taxonomicName id="333431F13609DBBEAED538A8D0FA2270" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3449F866-C045-4154-92A0-F9A956507FD5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus atratus Garman 1895:140" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atratus">R. atratus Garman</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CF1C4E8BF6241B7305E2CD277A96237E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8750C858-4799-4685-9B2F-41CE4CA3B9B7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus ornatus Garman 1895:139" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ornatus">R. ornatus Garman</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9E2BDDC1B6F259BAEDE7B46A4D34C719" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:65F512B3-6450-4C16-8292-22BECCD09F81" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus rectocaudatus Fels &amp; de Rham 1981:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rectocaudatus">R. rectocaudatus Fels and de Rham</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D1A2DF6A1CAEEC621A1207846FC42FE7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3F82970E-059D-4190-BBBB-3CEAA8DF4B99" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus romeri Costa 2003:176" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="romeri">R. romeri Costa</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="F48FE0A2A414FB4CA0D095EF2B1558D6" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F695CCB-F36C-4D87-A484-3D422BB7A184" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus tecminae Thomerson, Nico &amp; Taphorn 1992:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tecminae">R. tecminae Thomerson, Nico and Taphorn</taxonomicName>
, and is herein termed 
<taxonomicName id="F789AF6EC64F870E5EC94A8E4FBA48C8" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3449F866-C045-4154-92A0-F9A956507FD5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus atratus Garman 1895:140" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atratus">Rivulus atratus species group</taxonomicName>
. Two new species of this group, collected in the upper Rio Negro basin, northern Brazil, are herein described.
</paragraph>
